          "display_name": null,
          "email": "mayank.gupta@amdocs.com",
          "username": "mayankg2703"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-10 17:37:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Alexis,\n\nCan you please suggest?\n\nI think of approach.\nSolution can be.\n\n1. Define all credentials inside as a part of consul environment or environment file of host OS i.e. setenv.bash.\n2. if its part of setenv.bash then it will published inside consul using tpl as a part of consul POD environment.\n3.change template file of consul and at initialization phase some kind of start.sh will called which will take these credentials and convert into base64 and replace inside of relative consul configuration file.\n\nBut i think we have to open separate task for this to align all credentials. \n\nThanks,\nMayank Gupta",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
